text: Porte-de-Benauge is a commune in the Gironde department in southwestern France. It was established on 1 January 2019 by merger of the former communes of Arbis (the seat) and Cantois.Arrêté préfectoral 28 September 2018 ==See also== *Communes of the Gironde department ==References== Category:Communes of Gironde Category:States and territories established in 2019
title: Porte-de-Benauge
